# Coding Conventions

## Frontend Conventions
- Use TypeScript for all new code
- Components should be function components with hooks
- Place reusable components in `components/` directory
- Use named exports for components: `export function ComponentName()`
- Keep components focused and single-responsibility
- Use CSS modules for component-specific styles
- Place page components in `pages/` directory
- Use custom hooks for shared logic

## Backend Conventions
- Follow NestJS module structure
- Use decorators for route and controller definitions
- Place business logic in services
- Use DTOs for request/response validation
- Implement proper error handling
- Use dependency injection
- Follow RESTful API design principles

## General Guidelines
- Write meaningful commit messages
- Document complex logic with comments
- Use consistent naming conventions
- Keep functions small and focused
- Write unit tests for critical functionality
- Use proper error handling
- Follow the DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) principle
